summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2006 TRAVEL SUPREME MOTOR HOME. THE CONTACT STATED THAT A MECHANIC ADVISED THAT THE PARKING BRAKES WERE WIRED INCORRECTLY AND THE AIR TANKS NEED TO BE REPLACED. THERE WERE SEVERAL OTHER REPAIRS NEEDED SUCH AS DUMP VALVES, TOY HAULER AND THE LIFT ARMS NEEDING REPLACEMENT. THERE WAS ALSO FRACTURED WELDS FOUND THAT NEEDED REPLACING IN ADDITION TO THE HOT WATER SYSTEM NEEDING TO BE REPLACED. THE VEHICLE WAS INCLUDED IN NHTSA CAMPAIGN ID NUMBER: 07V408000 (EQUIPMENT). THE MANUFACTURER WAS NOT NOTIFIED OF THE MULTIPLE FAILURES. THE APPROXIMATE FAILURE AND CURRENT MILEAGE WAS 41,600.
FUEL LINE RUPTURE, ENGINE MANUFACTURE WAS AWARD OF THIS PROBLEM AND FAILED TO NOTIFY ME AS TO THE POTENTIAL HAZARD.  *TR
